Class GameSession

java.lang.Object
main.java.com.team.game.model.GameSession
public final class GameSession extends Object
Immutable data model representing a single game session.

Each session belongs to a user and tracks progress (score, strikes), the mode played, and timestamps for when the session started and ended.

    • GameSession

      public GameSession(int id, int userId, GameMode mode, Instant startedAt, Instant endedAt, int score, int strikes, boolean completed)
      Constructs a new GameSession instance.
      Parameters:
      id - unique identifier for this session
      userId - ID of the user who owns this session
      mode - the GameMode played
      startedAt - timestamp when the session began
      endedAt - timestamp when the session ended (nullable)
      score - total score achieved
      strikes - number of incorrect answers recorded
      completed - true if the session has ended, false if ongoing
